name: The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater
dealTitle: COMP  for $20.00 - 1-Woman Show "Eating Pasta Off the Floor" With Maria Grazia Affinito
dealinfo: In this hilariously heartfelt one-woman show, Maria hopes a trip to her mom's hometown in Italy will shed some light on their volatile relationship. Maybe singing arias at at full voice in the supermarket and offering to sell your daughter are just quaint traditions from the Old World? But even old friends in Italy are aghast when Mom starts flinging pasta and bad poetry. Developed by Maria Grazia Affinito with David Ford at The Marsh, Eating Pasta Off the Floor has been performed for sold-out audiences at Fringe Festivals in Orlando, Santa Cruz, Edmonton, Winnipeg, Vancouver and San Francisco, taking home several awards. Affinito brings all the charm and humor of growing up in a poor immigrant family to a show the  Orlando Sentinel  compares to "a heart-to-heart over the kitchen table. " Pull up a seat and settle in when it comes to The Marsh San Francisco MainStage Theater as part of The Marsh Discovery Series.

name: The Marsh Berkeley
dealTitle: COMP  for $20.00 - "Colette Uncensored": Acclaimed One-Woman Show Looks at Famed "Gigi" Author
dealinfo: Collette Uncensored , a one-woman show that can now be seen at The Marsh Berkeley, takes an in-depth look at the trailblazing French novelist Colette. The Nobel Prize-winning author of  Cheri ,  Duo  and, most famously,  Gigi , which was adapted into the blockbuster 1958 film directed by Hollywood maverick Vincente Minnelli, Colette was also an environmentalist and an ardent feminist whose progressive beliefs (particularly as they pertained to sexual liberation) made her a willing enemy of polite society. Actress Lorri Holt ( Patch Adams ) brings Colette to vivid life on stage, providing an overview of the writer's life while displaying her extraordinary gifts for storytelling, social commentary and humor. Come find out for yourself why the  The San Francisco Examiner  raved, "It's immediately clear how effortlessly this consummate actress channels early-20th-century French novelist Colette . Holt simply embodies the rebellious character in all her (ever-so-French) self-confidence, vulnerability and sensual charm. "

name: The Marsh San Francisco
dealTitle: COMP  for $20.00 - "From Piss to Bliss": A One-Woman Ode to San Francisco
dealinfo: The Marsh Upstairs Studio Theater presents comedian and storyteller Ady Lady in  From Piss to Bliss , a riotous tour through 21st-century San Francisco and its best intentions. In this hilarious new solo show, Ady doggedly seeks out higher consciousness amidst the often deranged reality of modern day life. She desperately seeks enlightenment on Muni, discovers the powerful spiritual lessons of riding Segways and utterly exhausts herself on a breast cancer walk, while trying to answer the question "Can we be our best selves during our worst moments?"

name: San Francisco 49ers
dealTitle: Preseason Football: Houston Texans vs. San Francisco 49ers With Lower-Level Seating
dealinfo: Head to Levi's Stadium and get your first glimpse at the 2016 San Francisco 49ers with great lower-level seats. The team is eager for a fresh start this season, and will do so with new coach Chip Kelly and first-round draft picks DeForest Buckner and Joshua Garnett. See how the team stacks up against the 2015 AFC South champion Houston Texans, led by head coach Bill O'Brien. No matter what the outcome, you and your friends and family will enjoy a fun day in awesome lower-level seats at one of the NFL's most spectacular venues. You can grab a beer and a snack at Bourbon Steak on the ground level, enjoy a crab sandwich on grilled sourdough bread from the concession stand or chow down on one of the 24 other locally sourced menu items on hand.

name: Victoria Theatre
dealTitle: $20.00  for $50.00  - Tony-Winning Musical Comedy "La Cage Aux Folles"
dealinfo: A boisterous and vibrant portrait of love in a nontraditional family,  La Cage Aux Folles  has been one of Broadway's biggest hits for more than 30 years, earning nine Tony Awards, including Best Musical and Best Revival. This heart-warming musical comedy invites you into the lives of Georges and his lover Albin, who plays female impersonator Zaza at the couple's popular St. Tropez drag nightclub. Problems arise when Georges' 25-year-old son comes home with his fianc. e and her conservative parents. Watch as the flamboyant couple's family dynamic gets hilariously turned upside down. Written by Harvey Fierstein, the musical features Jerry Herman's beloved score -- including "The Best of Times Is Now" and "I Am What I Am. " Get in on the wig-flying fun as  La Cage Aux Folles  closes out the Bay Area Musicals season at San Francisco's Victoria Theatre.

name: SuperHero Street Fair
dealTitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Superhero & Electronic Music Street Fair: Climbing Wall, Live Cartoon Art & More
dealinfo: Bust out your cape and tights and get ready to party, superhero style. With comic art exhibits, exciting activities, live music and costumes galore, the SuperHero Street Fair San Francisco is a supercharged day of fun along the waterfront boardwalk. Setting the soundtrack to the day is a slew of electronic musicians pumping out beats on seven stages and 11 sound camps. They're sure to get you psyched up as you check out jaw-dropping art installations such as the laser-cut sculptures of "Hybycozo," the oasis of gigantic illuminated flowers that is "Solar Freaking Galaxies," and the 50-foot, interactive cube arrangement titled "Mini Squared. " Make your way over to the Jack Kirby Museum to pay homage to "The King of Comics," who co-created Captain America, the Fantastic Four, Silver Surfer, the X-Men, the Hulk, the Avengers and many more classic characters. The Cartoon Art Museum will also be open, and there will be superhero photo ops aplenty, food vendors, a full bar and more.

name: Sixth Course
dealTitle: $41.00 for $68.00 - Craft Chocolate Walking Tour: The Sweet Side of the Mission District
dealinfo: San Francisco's Mission District is bursting with rich history -- chocolate history, that is. Join along on an Edible Excursions tour that'll take you to several of the innovative chocolate and confection factories that have called the District home through the years. During the three-hour walking tour, you'll get to enjoy hand-crafted chocolate tastes from new hot spots and neighborhood institutions, meet the chocolate-makers and chocolatiers behind these popular Mission District businesses, and sample their delectable signature offerings.

name: Body Chemistry Studio
dealTitle: Body Chemistry Studio - Five Classes
dealinfo: Five Pilates Reformer classes _Valid for new clients only_

name: Public Works
dealTitle: COMP  for $12.00 - "Speechless": Speakers and Comics Give Off-the-Cuff Pro Presentations
dealinfo: You've seen presentations all of your life . but none like this.  Speechless  is a combination live show and corporate training phenomenon that puts presenters on stage to deliver a PowerPoint presentation without any knowledge of the slides or decks. The improv "pro" talks get underway at San Francisco's Public Works. Watch your favorite tech industry gods and comedians turn their ad libbed presentations into a competitive showdown. Each presenter will be assigned a topic at random -- from a TED Talk to a startup pitch to a self-help seminar. You'll help choose the name of the talk, then the presenters will do their best to get through them like experts. Fusing technology with top notch talent,  Speechless  is the comedy show for the Web 2.0 world.

name: Golden Gate Park
dealTitle: $37.50 for $75.00 - San Francisco Golden Gate Park Segway Tour
dealinfo: Explore San Francisco's vast and scenic Golden Gate Park -- which is actually bigger than NYC's Central Park at more than 1,000 acres -- while cruising along on an ultra-cool Segway. After a brief training session in which you'll learn the ins and outs of maneuvering your vehicle safely, you'll set out for a 2.5-hour tour of the park led by your narrator, who will reveal the history and tales behind this man-made oasis in the city. It's the best -- and most fun -- way to see all that the park has to offer.

name: Oasis
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - Cabaret Icon Our Lady J Gives Gospel Music a Glitzy Twist
dealinfo: Get ready to testify when New York cabaret icon Our Lady J and her Train-To-Kill Gospel Choir sing their original twist on famed pop songs at San Francisco's Oasis. A member of the writing staff on the groundbreaking Golden Globe and Emmy-winning series  Transparent , Our Lady J is also a former classical pianist who worked as a musical director for stars like Cyndi Lauper, Debbie Harry, Lady Gaga, Elaine Stritch and others. She became famed on the underground scene for her signature live shows, giving traditional church music a glitzy rock twist with her soul-shaking voice and prodigious piano skills. Find out why Dolly Parton said, "I just love listening to Our Lady J," when you attend this performance of  Gospel for the Godless , with special guest Derek Schmidt.

name: Stud Bar
dealTitle: $5.00  for $10.00  - Red Hots Burlesque: Striptease & Variety Show at The Stud
dealinfo: For more than a decade, the performers of Red Hots Burlesque have been bumping and grinding their way across the best stages in New York and San Francisco. Now the United States' longest-running queer burlesque show's moving their popular Friday night extravaganza to the Stud, San Francisco's oldest gay bar! Voted San Francisco's hottest happy hour by  SF Weekly , Red Hots features burlesque's signature striptease numbers, along with comedy, drag, live music, death-defying aerials, acrobatics and more. This all-inclusive troupe boasts talent from every gender, size, cultural background and performance style, and with a rotating roster of international performers, you're guaranteed to see an all-new show each and every time.

name: Nourse Theater
dealTitle: $50.00 for $63.00 - Ryan Stiles & Greg Proops in "Whose Live Anyway?"
dealinfo: From the dark comedy clubs of America's major cities to primetime television screens nationwide,  Whose Line Is It Anyway?  -- a show where "everything's made up and the points don't matter" -- brought improvisational comedy to the masses like never before. Now, the Emmy-nominated comedy sensation is coming to the stage at the Nourse Theatre in San Francisco, featuring quick-thinking veteran improvisers Ryan Stiles, Greg Proops, Jeff Davis and Joel Murray. See some of your favorite  Whose Line  games like "Scenes from a Hat" or "Questions Only" along with some new ones -- and be sure to bring suggestions for a chance to join the cast onstage.

name: Davies Symphony Hall
dealTitle: "An American Maverick": Composer Steve Reich Celebrates His 80th Birthday
dealinfo: The San Francisco Symphony celebrates Pulitzer-winning composer Steve Reich's 80th birthday with "An American Maverick", a special event hosted by musical director Michael Tilson Thomas. The master of minimalism and longtime friend of the Symphony will be honored by a pair of Grammy-winning ensembles: string quartet Kronos Quartet and contemporary sextet Eighth Blackbird. The Davies Symphony Hall concert will also feature an appearance by Reich himself. You'll hear masterpieces like "Different Trains" and "Double Sextet", along with commentary and personal anecdotes narrated by Thomas.

name: Herbst Theatre at the San Francisco War Memorial Building
dealTitle: $10.50  for $20.00  - Asian/Pacific Islander LGBTQ Beauty Pageant "Runaway XXVIII: Intergalactic"
dealinfo: Get ready to uncover all the fabulousness in the universe as the Gay Asian Pacific Alliance (GAPA) Foundation's  Runway XXVIII: Intergalactic  makes a crash landing onto San Francisco's Herbst Theatre. Hosted by Miss GAPA 2012 Jezebel Patel and Mister GAPA 2013 Whitney Queers, this annual beauty pageant kicks into light speed and launches into a galaxy far, far away as a group of other-worldly Candydates battle for this year's title of Mister and Miss GAPA. There'll be surprise guest judges, a talent competition and, of course, an opportunity to see these contestants harness the power of the FIERCE to strut their stuff on the runway. Don't miss out on this unforgettable night of empowerment as proceeds benefit GAPA Foundation's Student Scholarship and Community Grants Programs.

name: The Rueff at A.C.T's Strand Theater
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - World Premiere of Teen-Centric Drama: "Top of the Pyramid"
dealinfo: After their school district in Ferguson loses accreditation, a group of friends decides to get bused across the tracks to a high school in a thoroughly unfamiliar environment. This decision comes with a series of significant trials and tribulations, which some of these friends navigate far better than others -- all of which threatens not only their friendships but also their very futures. With its cast of talented and diverse young actors from the A. C. T. Education & Community Programs, Destiny Arts in Oakland, and the Young Conservatory, this world premiere sheds insightful light on the challenges faced by so many modern teenagers. Enjoy  Top of the Pyramid  at The Rueff at A. C. T. 's Strand Theater in San Francisco.

name: Second City Tours-The Yard at Mission Rock
dealTitle: $50.00 for $100.00 - SOMA Stroll Food & Drink Tour Explores Innovative Eateries
dealinfo: Tour one of the hottest neighborhoods in the city and learn more about the booming restaurant scene south of Market Street on this SOMA Stroll Food & Drink Tour. You'll visit at least four innovative restaurants on this two-and-a-half-hour food tour through San Francisco's booming SOMA district, home to exciting conceptual eateries and bars. Bring your culinary sense of adventure and be prepared to explore a wide range of cutting-edge tastes, fabulous flavors and inventive cocktails.

name: Bindlestiff Studio
dealTitle: $15.00  for $30.00  - "I Love You, You're Perfect, Now Change": The Hit Musical Celebration of Love
dealinfo: From single life to dating to marriage to the end of relationships, the charming musical revue  I Love You, You're Perfect, Now Change  explores all of love's stages with humor, emotion and insight. As the show journeys from pickup lines to newborns and even to love amongst the geriatric set, it offers something that everyone who's ever been in or out of love will be able to identify with. The show's New York production was the second longest-running musical in off-Broadway history, and now it comes to San Francisco's Bindlestiff Studio.

name: Beer Basement
dealTitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - Craft Beer & Comedy at Stand-Up Show "The Setup"
dealinfo: Craft beer and comedy merge harmoniously in the Beer Basement at Ales Unlimited, where  The Setup  draws some of the funniest local and nationally touring stand-ups in the business. The space is small and cozy but the hops and the laughs are big, with performers hailing from such comedic institutions as  Comedy Bang Bang , San Francisco Sketchfest and The Comedy Store. So select a drink from Ales Unlimited's world-class selection of microbrews, wines and specialty cocktails and head downstairs for truly underground experience in the heart of the Tenderloin.

dealTitle: $10 OFF Any Purchase Total of $50. or More! General Grocery Items, Including Deli Service COunter, Beer & Wine.
disclaimer: Excludes Meat/FIsh Department and the Specialty Bakery Department. One Coupon per Customer, Per Visit. Please Present Coupon upon Checkout. Limited Time Offer. Coupons may not be combined with any other offer. Coupon void if altered.

name: Beyond Escape, LLC
dealTitle: $18.00 for $28.00 - "Trapped in a Room With a Zombie": You Have to Find the Way Out!
dealinfo: Don't just sit in a dark theater and watch a zombie movie on the screen. For this interactive experience, you're trapped in a room -- and a hungry zombie is there too, chained to the wall. Every five minutes, a buzzer sounds and the zombie's chain is released a few more inches. You and up to 11 other adventurers have just one hour to escape the room or risk getting eaten! Hidden in the room is a key that will unlock the door to your freedom. You and your fellow zombie bait must work together to locate numerous clues and solve riddles. It's perfect for a thrilling night out with friends, a really cool date night, or just to have a blast by yourself while meeting new people -- because cheating death-by-zombie tends to create fast friendships.

name: The Warfield
dealTitle: $37.13  for $62.50  - Public Enemy, Ice-T & Naughty by Nature: "The Art of Rap" Tour
dealinfo: Some of hip-hop's most powerful voices both on and off the stage hit the road for  The Art of Rap  tour, which makes a stop at The Warfield in San Francisco for a night of fiery rhymes and insightful knowledge. Golden age of rap superstars Public Enemy lead the bill, with booming MC Chuck D and whirlwind Flavor Flav performing huge hits like "Shut 'Em Down" and "911 Is a Joke. " Also hitting the stage is veteran rapper Ice-T, who was the first major voice to come out of L. A. with songs like "Colors" and "High Rollers," plus Naughty by Nature, who had classic party anthems "O. P. P. " and "Hip Hop Hooray," and hip-hop pioneers GrandMaster Melle Mel and Scorpio.

name: PianoFight
dealTitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - Dance Plus Laughs in the "Super Serious Postmodern Dance Variety Hour"
dealinfo: Postmodern dance just  sounds  so highbrow and inaccessible to those of us who aren't . highbrow. PianoFight's  Super Serious Postmodern Dance Variety Hour  removes the highbrow and amps up the decidable accessible fun with a show that combines heavy-hitting dance talent with a crack team of comedy writers and performers. Music video dance karaoke? Check. A dance drinking game? Check. The best modern dance solos in the bay? You betcha. The incomparable choreographer Louis Acquisto hosts this show that features some of the Bay Area's most amazing young artists. See it and have a super-serious good time.

name: EXIT Café
dealTitle: $10.00 for $25.00 - Juggling, Stunts & Sleight-of-Hand at "Street Magic Live"
dealinfo: San Francisco's thrilling street performance scene comes inside at this showcase of magic, juggling and stunts by local practitioners. In the intimate Exit Theater Cafe, you'll feast your eyes on the likes of Frisco Fred, whose juggling mastery has appeared on such TV shows as A&E's  An Evening at the Improv. He'll be joined by Lynx the Animator, a sleight-of-hand dynamo who wows crowds with his sly wit and lightning-fast hands, and the versatile entertainer Chase, who melds magic, mind-ding and acrobatics with the Southern charm of a native Georgian.

name: Eddy St Theatreplex - The EXIT Theatre
dealTitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "The Magic of Ryan Kane": Magic Champ Conjures Up Daring Show
dealinfo: A recent winner of the San Francisco Stage Magic Competition and a finalist at the Rooster T. Feather's and Wharf Room Comedy competitions, Ryan Kane will astound and amuse in his show,  Please Enjoy Responsibly. Kane began honing his craft as a teenager on the streets of Old Sacramento where he attracted audiences with his deft magic and charming personality. In his show, minds are read, whiskey bottles appear out of nowhere and a paintball gun is fired at the man responsible for it all. Don't miss his San Francisco appearance at the EXIT Theatre.

name: Ólafur Arnalds at The Regency Ballroom
dealTitle: $59.50  for $93.50  - The Mick Fleetwood Blues Band: Roots Music, Mac & More
dealinfo: Mick Fleetwood may've co-founded one of the most successful and respected rock acts of all time in Fleetwood Mac, but he confesses to being a blues man at heart. So the acclaimed British drummer went out and created yet another eponymous group, The Mick Fleetwood Blues Band. It's fronted by singer-guitarist Rick Vito, and jams through original tunes, early era Mac ("Oh Well," "Rattlesnake Shake") and vintage Americana classics like "Shake Your Money Maker" and "When the Levee Breaks. " The quartet's live album,  Blue Again!  scored a Grammy nomination as Best Traditional Blues Album, and this tour includes a prime slot at the Telluride Blues Festival, behind Joe Walsh. Don't miss this stop at the Regency Ballroom in San Francisco.

name: Our Little Comedy Theater
dealTitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - "A-List Comedy": International Stand-Up
dealinfo: Located just a few blocks from Union Square in the hip Tenderloin district,  A-List Comedy  offers an intimate night of laughter. The 30-seat club has hosted up-and-coming performers who've been featured on Comedy Central, HBO, BET, Stand-Up Live and London Weekend Television. Five to six comedians will take the stage during the 90-minute show to provide you with an international mix of terrific comedy, while supporting Global Women Intact. Plus, the SF Downtown Comedy Theater (also known as Our Little Comedy Theater) is a BYOB venue, so you can bring your own drinks.

name: Extranomical Tours
dealTitle: $70.00 for $140.00 - Customizable Wine Country Tour: A Full-Day Trip for Wine Lovers
dealinfo: Check out the best of Napa and Sonoma counties on a full-day, semi-private tour of the Northern California wine country. With small groups and the ability to request and choose from several different destination options, this semi-customizable tour offers visits to four to six wineries, with a wide variety of experiences and tastings. Knowledgeable and friendly guides make for a relaxed and educational excursion through one of the most scenic regions in the entire country and will help put together a great day of sightseeing and sampling.

name: Marrakech Magic Theater
dealTitle: $22.50 for $45.00 - Magic & Comedy From San Francisco's Peter Morrison at Marrakech Magic Theater
dealinfo: Marrakech Magic Theater features world-renowned sleight-of-hand magician Peter Morrison in a highly interactive show in its intimate 42-seat theater. A featured performer at the world-famous Magic Castle in Hollywood, Morrison combines mind-blowing magic, intriguing feats of mentalism and laugh-out-loud humor in a fast-paced 75-minute show -- and audience participation makes each performance different. Make sure you get there early to enjoy Morrison's pre-show tableside magic in the Oasis Lounge.

name: The Creativity Theater
dealTitle: $15.00 for $30.00 - "The Rules": A "Late" Coming-of-Age Tale of Love & Friendship
dealinfo: While all is fair in love and war, it wouldn't hurt to have some sure-fire guidelines on how to find the perfect match -- especially if you're three friends caught in a tangled love triangle in  The Rules. When Ana, Julia and Mehr all fall for the same man, they are forced to examine the complicated rules of their friendship within a technologically-saturated society. Inspired by the dating guide  The Rules: The Time Tested Secrets for Capturing The Heart of Mr. Right , this "late" coming of age story dives into the meaning of love and takes a close look at the endless pursuit of happy endings. Written by Dipika Guha,  The Rules  makes its world premiere at The Creativity Theater.

name: Feinstein's at The Nikko
dealTitle: James Tormxe9, Son of Legendary Mel Tormxe9, at Feinstein's at the Nikko
dealinfo: Son of three-time Grammy winner Mel Torm\xe9, uniquely gifted singer James Torm\xe9 possesses a voice as smooth as silk. Known for his showmanship as much as his vocal gifts -- he's been quoted as saying, "I want to give them a night they'll never forget" -- James was praised as "the best male jazz singer to come along in 20 years" by Verve Records president Chuck Mitchell. James' music infuses older jazz classics with soul and R&B; influences of today, appealing to young and old audiences alike. Awarded the Chuck Niles Jazz Music Award in 2007, his debut album, "Love for Sale", topped both the iTunes and Amazon jazz charts. See James make his San Francisco debut at Feinstein's at the Nikko.

name: Feinstein's at the Nikko
dealTitle: $23.61 for $33.73 - Suede -- Jazz/Pop Chanteuse at Feinstein's at the Nikko
dealinfo: Imagine a cross between Adele, Diana Krall and Bette Midler and you might get some idea of Suede's unique musical talents. Sassy, smooth and intoxicating, this consummate entertainer was Joan Rivers' opening act, and she sings original material and pop, blues and jazz standards like nobody you've ever heard. From a cappella to belting blues -- and even some of her smokin' trumpet solos -- Suede delivers it all with her own unique blend of warmth, wit and musical artistry. Grab your chance to see this resident of New York and Cape Cod when she visits San Francisco for two nights at Feinstein's at the Nikko.

name: Buddha Bliss Therapeutic Massage
dealTitle: Buddha Bliss Therapeutic Massage - 60-Minute Therapeutic Massage
dealinfo: One 60-minute therapeutic massage _Valid for new clients and existing clients who havent visited the studio in the past six months_

name: Biscuits & Blues
dealTitle: $7.50  for $15.00  - Biscuits & Blues: Great Music and Down-Home Grub
dealinfo: From its top-quality live musical guests to its exceptional Southern cuisine, Biscuits & Blues is the perfect San Francisco spot to enjoy a night of down-home entertainment nearly every night of the week. Located in the heart of the theater district, this intimate venue hosts the best regional and national blues and jazz acts in a comfortable, close-up setting that's open to all ages. Voted America's No. 1 blues nightclub by The Blues Foundation and the Bay Area Blues Society, it's also known for serving up some of the best fried chicken in the entire region, not to mention California wines, microbrews and specialty cocktails.

name: Commonwealth Club of Calif
dealTitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - Former San Francisco Giant Jeremy Affeldt on Baseball and Advocacy
dealinfo: Jeremy Affeldt's professional baseball career spanned 14 years with the Kansas City Royals, the Colorado Rockies, the Cincinnati Reds and, for his last seven years, with the San Francisco Giants (including all three Giants World Champion teams in 2010, 2012 and 2014). Since retiring from his very successful Major League career in 2015, he's turned his attention to philanthropic and humanitarian efforts, actively working to end human trafficking and modern-day slavery and feeding the hungry at home and around the globe. He co-founded Generation Alive, a non-profit organization that works to teach and inspire a generation of young people to serve others. He's written a book about his work, and he's a regular contributor to the Huffington Post and Medium. com. Be inspired by Affeldt's work on and off the field when he speaks at the Commonwealth Club in San Francisco.

name: Phoenix Theatre San Francisco
dealTitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - "Barbarella": Stage Adaptation of Sexy Sci-Fi Classic
dealinfo: Roger Vadim's ultra sexy sci-fi cult classic makes the intergalactic leap from screen to stage in an all-new adaptation that is sure to be out of this world. The year is 40,000 and scientist Durand Durand has gone missing somewhere within the Tau Ceti region. To ensure his deadly Positronic Ray doesn't fall into the wrong hands, Earth sends the voluptuous bounty hunter Barbarella on a super top-secret rescue mission. Along the way, she encounters various alien beings who wish to sleep with her. Now the Double Rated Star Astronavagatrix will have to use her brains, brawn and everything else she's got in order to save the entire universe from impending doom. Catch all the risqu.  outer space action when  Barbarella  makes a crash landing onto San Francisco's Phoenix Theatre.

name: Firescape Theatre
dealTitle: $15.00 for $30.00 - Family Secrets Revealed in "Emmitt and Ava"
dealinfo: One spring afternoon in a Venice, Calif., living room, families meet, strangers converge and secrets are revealed. Communication, even between those who are highly motivated to communicate, is tested again and again.  Emmitt and Ava  is a contemporary tale of love and loss and the sometimes surprising kinship between humor and tragedy. The play reminds us how much we need to simply be there for one another, or face losing what is most important to us all -- our humanity. Catch  Emmitt and Ava  at San Francisco's Firescape Theatre.

name: San Francisco Playhouse
dealTitle: $25.00  for $50.00  - "City of Angels": Broadway's Musical Nod to Film Noir
dealinfo: Set in Los Angeles in the late 1940s,  City of Angels  tells the story of a novelist struggling to turn his hard-boiled detective novel into a movie. Weaving together the novelist's actual life with the story of his fictional P. I. hero, the San Francisco Playhouse's production is a stylish nod to the golden age of Hollywood and film noir, where the colorful real world collides with the black-and-white "reel" world. The winner of six Tony Awards, including Best Musical, this show was co-written by Broadway legend Cy Coleman and  M*A*S*H  creator Larry Gelbart.

name: Union Square
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - Emperor Norton's Fantastic SF Time Machine Walking Tour
dealinfo: Take a tour through San Francisco's history with one of its most colorful characters. Emperor Norton was a prominent businessman who lost it all on a bad investment. He responded to his failure by declaring himself "Emperor of the United States and Protector of Mexico. " Rather than dismissing him, San Francisco embraced him, treating him as royalty and accepting his self-created currency. Tour guide Joseph Amster incorporates his journalistic and acting talents to provide a one-of-a-kind tour, taking on the persona of Emperor Norton and introducing you to the history of the city's most unique and interesting sites through the eyes of this larger-than-life unofficial city mascot.

name: Shelton Theater
dealTitle: COMP  for $17.00 - Secret Improv Society: Comedy & Song in High-Energy Revue
dealinfo: With their successful blend of improvised comedy and song continuing to entertain the semi-masses on a weekly basis, the Secret Improv Society's popular theatrical shows are not so clandestine anymore. A bunch of San Francisco's best improvisers, comedians and musicians often come out to play with the sharp-witted regular cast, too. It all results in a fast-paced, high-energy revue, featuring plenty of audience input and interaction. Volunteers can even join the fun onstage. No two shows are ever identical, so repeat visits to this Shelton Theater laugh fest are strongly suggested.

name: Un-Scripted Theater Company
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - An Improvised Love Letter to San Francisco: "Life in SF"
dealinfo: From Silicon Valley techies to Berkeley hipsters,  Life in SF  creates an improvised play about the city's unique and beloved characters. Each night, the Un-Scripted Theater Company presents a San Francisco-fueled, one of a kind theater experience based on audience suggestions. Every show is unique, so you never know what Bay Area characters you'll see on stage. Voted Best Theater Company in 2008 by the  SF Bay Guardian , the Un-Scripted Theater Company has staged over 40 productions since 2002 in a variety of genres like stage plays, narrative long-form and improv comedy. Witness a view of San Francisco from a theater that performs and thrives in the heart of the city itself.

name: Custom Made Theatre
dealTitle: $10.00  for $20.00  - Stacy Ross Stars in Psychological Thriller "The Thrush & the Woodpecker"
dealinfo: Danger and vicious humor collide in this Custom Made Theatre Co. production of  The Thrush & the Woodpecker , starring the Bay Area's own Stacy Ross. In this spine-tingling revenge thriller from playwright Steve Yockey, Brenda Hendricks tries to repair a fractured relationship with her son Noah, who has hastily returned home from college following an act of vandalism. When a mysterious visitor arrives at their remote Northern California home bearing dangerous secrets from Brenda's past, the three find themselves on a collision course with betrayal and revenge. Get ready for a white-knuckled thriller filled with plot twists, gasps and gripping theatricality with  The Thrush & the Woodpecker .

name: Fume Blanc Commodore
dealTitle: $44.50 for $89.00 - San Francisco Bay Midnight Party Cruise Aboard a Luxury Yacht
dealinfo: Take the party to the water this summer with a midnight party cruise aboard the fabulous Fume Blanc Commedore. With stunning views of the San Francisco skyline, Treasure Island, Alcatraz, the Bay Bridge and the Golden Gate Bridge, this is the kind of experience you won't be able to replicate at a club or hotel. Featuring two DJs on three decks playing the best in club music, a fully stacked cash bar and a hot group of fellow partiers, this three-hour party cruise is your ticket to a fabulous time on the water. VIP admission includes priority boarding, a complimentary glass of champagne, first access to unreserved seating, a coat check and a commemorative captain's hat.

name: Cabernet Sauvignon Commodore Yacht
dealTitle: $22.50 for $45.00 - "Pier Pressure" Memorial Day Yacht Party Cruise
dealinfo: With six DJs, a cash bar and breathtaking views of the San Francisco skyline, Treasure Island, Alcatraz, the Bay Bridge, the Golden Gate Bridge and more, this Memorial Day Sunday cruise aboard the luxury Cabernet Sauvignon Commodore Yacht is the perfect way to wrap up the official summer season.  Pier Pressure  features music on four separate decks with the best in open format and house/EDM, along with several fully stocked bars and a hot group of fun-minded individuals for your partying pleasure.

name: Huntington Park
dealTitle: $22.50 for $45.00 - "The Whole Shebang": See Three of SF's Famous Neighborhoods
dealinfo: FOOT's flagship comedy walking tour,  The Whole Shebang,  is actually three fascinating tours of San Francisco squeezed into one three-hour excursion. See the best that Union Square, Chinatown and North Beach have to offer while learning about the Gold Rush, the railroad barons, the Great Earthquake and Fire, cable cars, movie locations, literature, architecture and much more from one of FOOT's friendly and knowledgeable guides. Along the way, you'll play games, answer questions and just generally have a great time.

name: Architecture Walking Tour - Galleria Park Hotel Lobby
dealTitle: $20.00 for $40.00 - San Francisco Architecture Walking Tour: Discover the City's Hidden Treasures
dealinfo: Discover the rich history of San Francisco architecture on Rick Evans' two-hour narrated walking tour, loaded with secret gems and hidden jewels. In addition to learning about the history of the architecture in the Financial District, you'll also see the city's newest skyscrapers, as well as rooftop gardens and other hidden public spaces that few people know about. Whether you're a longtime resident or visiting for the first time, you'll see this stunning city in a whole new way.

name: The Variety Preview Theater
dealTitle: $7.50 for $15.00 - Fresh Line-Ups Featuring San Francisco's Best Stand-Up Comedians
dealinfo: Long home to an electric comedy scene, the Bay Area has spawned some of the biggest names in stand-up, from Margaret Cho to Patton Oswalt, and it continues to breed the next generation of hilarious stars, like Vah.  Hove and Chris Schiappacasse. Every Friday, get a sneak peek of who is up-and-coming in San Francisco's comedy scene, when a fresh line-up of San Francisco's best comics -- including many who have been seen performing on HBO, NBC, Comedy Central and more -- take the stage at the beautiful Variety Preview Theater in downtown San Francisco's iconic Hobart Building. Once there, splurge on food and drinks for a good cause. Proceeds from the sales go to Variety Children's Charity of Northern California.

name: Commonwealth Club of CA
dealTitle: $12.50 for $25.00 - Author Moira Weigel Asks, Is Dating Dead?
dealinfo: In her book  Labor of Love: The Invention of Dating , Author Moira Weigel writes, "All humans long for others with whom to share our lives. " Her book dives into the deep end of dating and mating practices through the ages, from the era of courtships and calling cards through arranged marriages and up to the current widespread use of dating apps like Tinder, Bumble and OKCupid. While many today wonder if dating is dead, Weigel instead looks at the history of dating and analyzes whether modern life has complicated and even ruined the art of courtship. Whether you're dating someone or looking for someone, this talk at San Francisco's Commonwealth Club is sure to jump-start some intriguing conversation!

name: Cocoon Urban Day Spa
dealTitle: $99 -- SoMa Spa: Massage & Mani/Pedi, Reg. $202

name: Second City Tours-Mechanics’ Monument Plaza
address: Corner of Market, Bush and Battery Streets
dealTitle: $50.00 for $100.00 - Pub Crawl Explores San Francisco's History and Bars
dealinfo: More than a century before San Francisco became the glittering high-tech hub it is today, it was a rough-and-tumble frontier metropolis -- the largest city west of the Mississippi River, a major trading hub and the financial center of the California Gold Rush. The Ghost Ships and Gold Pub Crawl through downtown San Francisco blends history with happy hour, departing from Mechanics' Monument Plaza and stopping at four popular bars for cocktails, beer or wine in between authentic glimpses of the ships and the gold that built this city by the bay.

name: Utopia Cafe
dealTitle: $25.00  for $49.00  - Hunt Killers & Ghosts in San Francisco's Chinatown
dealinfo: Get to the bottom of a head-scratching murder case while enjoying an authentic five-course Chinese dinner at this Chinatown Murder Mystery dinner show at San Francisco's Utopia Caf. As you and your friends tuck into imperial egg rolls, sweet and sour pork, fried rice and fortune cookies, a group of professional performers will act out a live, interactive whodunit all around you -- and the first guest to crack the case goes home with a prize! Then, with dinner over and the guilty party brought to justice, it's time for a 90-minute walking ghost tour through Chinatown.

name: Great Star Theatre
dealTitle: $10.00  for $20.00  - Kat Robichaud's Misfit Cabaret: Magic & Maritime Marvels in "Whim-Sea"
dealinfo: Singer Kat Robichaud ( The Voice ) once again graces San Francisco's Great Star Theater to dive into  Whim-Sea , a night filled with decadence, bawdiness and damsels  not  in distress. Part of Robichaud's Misfit Cabaret theater series,  Whim-Sea  takes you on a journey through the beautiful briny sea. There, you'll hear the sweet shipwreck serenade of Rabbit Quinn and watch the stunning Frankie Fictitious hula into your heart. You'll also experience the strolling minstrel raconteur Justin Seagrave as he weaves stories of dragons and sea monsters, then catch burlesque teases performed both underwater and on dry land. Plus, there's a guest appearance by Dave Haaz-Baroque Shadow Circus Creature Theater during the July 14 performance.

name: Chiaroscuro Ristorante
dealTitle: Michelin Pick: 'Mind-Blowing' Italian Dinner for 2, Now $79
disclaimer: Valid for two or four diners exactly, depending on option purchased (cannot add additional diners to table). Not valid during special events, such as Restaurant Week. Dine-in only. Must be of legal age to consume alcohol. Seasonal items subject to change. Not valid on products. Cannot combine with other offers. Must use in one visit.
dealinfo: **$79 for a three-course dinner for two from the restaurant's nightly menu** (reg. $130) Each person receives one option from the following courses: antipasti; pasta or secondi; and dolci or formaggi The current dinner menu features grilled octopus with white beans and smoked pancetta puree; and braised short rib ravioli with mixed mushrooms and truffle parmigiano ** $155 for the same dinner for four people **(reg. $260) With the dinner options, Travelzoo members get 20% off a bottle of wine **$39 for lunch for two** including any one shared antipasto or insalate, and any two entrees, such as housemade potato gnocchi, grilled NY steak or balsamic glazed pork belly (reg. $72) ** $75 for lunch for four **(reg. $144) See the menus **[here](http://chiaroscurosf.com/our-menu/)**

name: Chinatown Food Tour at East West Bank
dealTitle: $39.00 for $60.00 - Chinatown Food Tour: Savor China's Culinary Treats
dealinfo: San Francisco's world famous Chinatown holds a wealth of exquisite flavors, but without insider knowledge it can be difficult to find those culinary secrets. Your Sidewalk Food Tours guide will lead you through the streets and alleys of Chinatown where you will enjoy five flavorful tastings, satisfying your appetite for the exotic. You'll try Cantonese pork buns, President Obama's favorite S. F. dim sum, Chef Han's authentic Szechuan cuisine, savory Peking duck and egg tarts cooked to a smooth flan-like perfection with a flakey crust. At the end of the tour, you'll know all of the best spots to eat and can return to enjoy Chinatown's food with confidence. Vegetarian substitutions can be arranged with advance notice.

name: The Purple Onion at Kells Irish Bar
dealTitle: $5.00 for $10.00 - "Women Gettin' Witty": All-Female Stand-Up at The Purple Onion
dealinfo: From stand-up pioneers like Joan Rivers and Roseanne Barr to modern alt-comedy heroes like Maria Bamford and Tig Notaro, women have been rocking the mic -- and giving their Y-chromosome counterparts a run for their money -- since the earliest days of stand-up. Now you can experience live comedy from tomorrow's next big comics at  Women Gettin' Witty , an all-female stand-up showcase at The Purple Onion at Kells Irish Bar. Hosted by Katy Karns and Trishna Saigal, this monthly comedy show features some of the Bay Area's funniest women bringing their wittiest musings about life, love and other four-letter words.

name: Punch Line Comedy Club
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - Comedy and Competition Collide in Stand-Up Showdown
dealinfo: No night of comedy is quite like  Joke or Get Off the Stage,  Punchline Comedy Club's special stand-up competition featuring some of the Bay Area's best and most seasoned performers. Hilarious comics go head-to-head in a game show-style format that will determine the night's funniest comedian. You start with five comedians, and over the course of four rounds, one performer is eliminated at a time. The best part? It's up to you to decide who moves on. Each comic will bring their A-game in an effort to make you laugh the most, so join host Samson Koletkar (CBS, NBC Bay Area) in crowning the funniest stand-up of the night. Some competitions are no laughing matter;  Joke or Get Off the Stage  is the exact opposite.

name: Palace of Fine Arts Theatre
dealTitle: $49.50  for $69.50  - Art Garfunkel ("The Sound of Silence," "Breakaway") Performs Live
dealinfo: As one half of the legendary duo Simon & Garfunkel, countertenor Art Garfunkel has made his mark on the worlds of folk and rock 'n' roll. Songs like "The Sound of Silence," "Mrs. Robinson," "The Boxer" and "Bridge over Troubled Water" are known to generations, and earned the duo a Rock and Roll Hall of Fame induction in 1990. Garfunkel has gone on to a successful solo career, releasing 12 acclaimed albums and scoring hits with "All I Know," "Bright Eyes" and "Breakaway. " Now, he's coming to the Palace of Fine Arts Theatre in San Francisco for a show you won't want to miss.

name: Ferry Building
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - "Emperor Norton's Fantastic San Francisco Waterfront Tour"
dealinfo: Spend a Sunday afternoon touring San Francisco's waterfront history alongside one of its most colorful characters. Emperor Norton was a prominent businessman who lost everything on a bad investment. Instead of throwing in the towel, he responded to his failure by declaring himself "Emperor of the United States and Protector of Mexico. " San Francisco embraced this quirky character, treating him as royalty and even accepting his self-created currency. Tour guide Joseph Amster incorporates his journalistic and acting talents to provide a one-of-a-kind tour in which he takes on the persona of Emperor Norton and introduces you to the history of the city's most unique and interesting sites through the eyes of this larger-than-life unofficial mascot. Over the course of just under three hours, you'll cover about two miles along the waterfront, from the historic Ferry Building to The Cannery.

name: Washington Square Park
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - "San Francisco Food Safari": Discover the Culinary Gems of North Beach
dealinfo: The  San Francisco Food Safari  offers you the chance to explore the city's neighborhoods in-depth and discover the best cuisine each area has to offer. This 2.5-hour tour focuses on the North Beach neighborhood, where Chef Joseph will offer his knowledge and insights on the top places to eat as well as the history and culture of the area. You'll have the chance to purchase whatever you'd like throughout this shopping tour, which takes you to Mara's Italian Pastries, Liguria Bakery, Molinari Deli and beyond. Each tour ends with a picnic lunch made up of the delicious treats you've purchased along the way. Chef Joseph began his culinary career at San Francisco's legendary Salmagundi. He was also the food critic at the Orange County and Long Beach  Blade  and  IN Los Angeles  magazines, has written food articles for magazines, worked as a caterer, taught cooking classes and is working on a book titled  Created in California: The Golden State's Gifts to Gastronomy .

name: Hornblower Yachts San Francisco
dealTitle: $50.62 for $84.38 - San Francisco Bay Cruise With Lunch Buffet
dealinfo: Whether you're a tourist or longtime resident, seeing San Francisco by sea is nothing short of spectacular, and there's no better way to experience it than aboard a Hornblower cruise of the bay. This two-hour excursion takes you past Alcatraz Island and under the Golden Gate and Bay Bridges, for stunning views of the city skyline and more. You'll also enjoy a lunch buffet served on board, with soda, juice, coffee and tea included. Wine, beer and cocktails will be available for purchase as well.

name: Fort Mason Center
dealTitle: COMP  for $40.00  - Scavenger Hunt "The Great Puzzle Adventure: The Will" Features Race Around San Francisco
dealinfo: Prepare for a puzzle-solving urban quest unlike any other in  The Great Puzzle Adventure: The Will. You and your "siblings" have five hours to solve the mysterous will left by your "father" that requires you to dash around San Francisco to find secret codes, people or hidden puzzle boxes that will help you decipher the will and discover the location of the fortune. Lace up your shoes and get ready for a supremely challenging scavenger hunt that will test your brain and your endurance!

name: Cobb's Comedy Club
dealTitle: $7.50 for $15.00 - "Full Throttle Comedy" With Michael Quu (MTV and Spike TV)
dealinfo: East Coast native Michael Quu (pronounced "Q") now makes his home in L. A., where he hones his high-energy routine on relationships, family and everyday life. He's appeared at The Laugh Factory, hosted a weekly show at The Comedy Store in Hollywood and now he brings his well-reviewed, nationally touring  Full Throttle Comedy Show  to Cobb's Comedy Club in San Francisco, where he'll introduce the best up-and-coming local stand-up comics. Don't miss your chance to check out these rising Bay Area stars.

name: SF Electric Tour Company
dealTitle: $37.50 for $75.00 - Glide Through San Francisco on a Segway Night Tour
dealinfo: Discover a unique way to explore San Francisco with a Segway night tour. After a 45-minute training session to get you familiar with Segway travel, you'll set off on an exciting guided excursion through North Beach (San Francisco's Little Italy), Chinatown, and down the Embarcadero Waterfront to Fisherman's Wharf. Among the many sights you'll take in along the way: Saints Peter and Paul Church, the Transamerica Pyramid, the Fisherman's Chapel, Ghirardelli Square, the National Maritime Museum and the lights of Alcatraz and the Bay Bridge. Your knowledgeable guide will point out many hidden gems along the way and fill you in on the colorful history behind these most distinctive San Francisco neighborhoods and attractions.

name: Madame Tussauds San Francisco
dealTitle: $10.00  for $20.00  - Madame Tussauds: Legendary Attraction Brings the Stars to SF
dealinfo: Get up-close and personal with your favorite celebrities, sports stars and historic icons at the famous Madame Tussauds at Fisherman's Wharf. You'll encounter lifelike wax figures as you attend a Hollywood A-list party, join the stars on set for famous film scenes, step onto the stage with chart-topping musicians, witness key moments in history and test your skills against top athletes. You'll also get to mingle with famous figures from right here in the Bay Area in the "Spirit of San Francisco" Room. Before you leave, take the chance to go behind the scenes to find out more about the dramatic and sometimes dark story of Marie Tussaud's life, and the legacy she left behind, complete with authentic items from the Madame Tussauds archive. Every step of the wax figure process is explained using footage by a special guest star.

name: San Francisco Dungeon
dealTitle: $10.00  for $20.00  - San Francisco Dungeon: The Dark Side of Bay Area History
dealinfo: The San Francisco Dungeon brings to life the authentic tales of the Bay Area's dark history using actors, special effects, gripping storytelling and 360.  sets. The hysterically horrible stories will take you through nine actor-led shows, during which you'll witness reenacted scenes from the colorful Gold Rush era to authentic tales about the Barbary Coast criminal gangs and Alcatraz. You may even get shanghaied by the infamous Shanghai Kelly himself! It's the ultimate live-action expedition. See, hear, touch, smell and feel the experience of early San Francisco as you move from show to show guided by professional actors. It's hilarious fun -- and sometimes a little scary!

name: California Sunset Cruise
dealTitle: $32.00 for $64.00 - Red and White Fleet's California Sunset Cruise
dealinfo: Enjoy a two-hour tour of San Francisco Bay, highlighted by romantic sunset views, live guitar music and a light appetizer buffet including sandwiches, fruit and cheese. You'll view the city's stunning skyline featuring Coit Tower and the Transamerica Pyramid, along with historic landmarks and the natural beauty of the Bay Area. This scenic cruise sails by Alcatraz and Angel Island National Park, under the Golden Gate Bridge and along the gorgeous Tiburon, Belvedere and Sausalito shores. One drink is included (alcoholic or nonalcoholic), and more drinks and snacks are available for purchase at the full on-board bar.

name: RocketBoat
dealTitle: $13.50 for $27.00 - RocketBoat: The Ultimate High-Speed Adventure on San Francisco Bay
dealinfo: RocketBoat is a high-speed, 30-minute thrill ride on San Francisco Bay. Roaring past the beautiful San Francisco skyline, RocketBoat screams down to Bay Bridge and near AT&T Park, where you'll thrill to the high-speed twists and turns, propelled by the boat's 2800-horsepower engines. A classic rock 'n' roll soundtrack adds to the fun. If you want to get wet, sit toward the back. You'll stay a bit drier if you sit in the middle or the front of the vessel. Wet or dry, this ride is fast and fun.

name: SF Bay Cruise Adventure
dealTitle: $15.00 for $30.00 - San Francisco Bay Cruise Adventure
dealinfo: Sail under the Golden Gate Bridge and along the San Francisco Bay's historic waterfront on Blue & Gold Fleet's Bay Cruise Adventure. This fully narrated one-hour tour features information and history on city landmarks and plenty of opportunities for taking pictures of the unobstructed views of the San Francisco skyline. Both indoor and outdoor seating is available, so you can experience the sights and sounds from out on deck or take it all in from the warmth and comfort of an interior seat -- either experience makes for a truly great San Francisco adventure.

name: Bridge 2 Bridge Cruise
dealTitle: $19.00 for $38.00 - Red and White Fleet's Bridge 2 Bridge Cruise, With Narration
dealinfo: Celebrate the impressive San Francisco Bay Bridge and its history -- which spans over 75 years -- by embarking on this 90-minute cruise that sails under both the Golden Gate and the Bay Bridges and passes by Alcatraz Island. Discover San Francisco history and landmarks via narrated headset audio in 16 available languages, which includes information about the city's natural history, architecture, Native American culture, and, of course, the building of the famous bridges. It's a stunning and informative way to experience the breathtaking views of the downtown skyline and its historic waterfront.

name: Golden Gate Bay Cruise
dealTitle: $15.00 for $30.00 - Red and White Fleet's Golden Gate Bay Cruise
dealinfo: This Red and White Fleet Cruise launched in 1939 as part of the Golden Gate International Exposition, and it's still entertaining visitors and locals alike more than 70 years later. After departing from historic Fisherman's Wharf, the ship sails along San Francisco's breathtaking waterfront, past the city's Maritime National Park, under the majestic Golden Gate Bridge, and around notorious Alcatraz Island, cruising by many other exciting sights as well on the one-hour voyage. Take advantage of the personal-headphone audio, available in 16 languages, to learn more about San Francisco's history and world-famous landmarks, while enjoying a full onboard bar with drinks, snacks and more.

name: Pacifica Spindrift Players Theatre
dealTitle: $10.00 for $20.00 - "God of Carnage": Tony-Winning Comedy of Bad Manners
dealinfo: God of Carnage , Yasmina Reza's comedy of (bad) manners, begins with two couples meeting to work things out after a playground altercation between their children. As the evening progresses, their behavior goes from civilized to outrageous as each couple tries to pin the blame on the other for the incident. From cutting dialogue to broad physical comedy,  God of Carnage  will defy your expectations at every turn, becoming more hilarious with every scene. Find out just how thin the line between civility and brutality really is in this production at the Muriel Watkin Performance Space in the Pacifica Spindrift Players Theatre.

address: Sausalito Yacht Harbor: Slip 907 100 Bay Street

Book fast!

name: Cafe Figaro
dealTitle: $29 & up -- Burlingame: Italian Dining for 2 at Cafe Figaro

name: Waterfront Hotel
dealTitle: $63.00 for $105.00 - "The Dinner Detective": An Interactive Mystery Dinner Show
dealinfo: A favorite across the country,  The Dinner Detective  serves up a tasty whodunit along with a seated four-course dinner. And since this popular comic murder mystery is set in the present day, you'll never know whether someone at your table is one of the talented cast of improvisers. In fact, everyone's a suspect, including you. The event starts out with a reception featuring tray-passed hors d'oeuvres, followed by the meal, which includes salad, an entree and dessert. Between courses you can expect plenty of murder, mayhem and hidden clues coming to light as you puzzle through the crime. The top sleuth even wins a prize package at the end of the evening -- not to mention serious bragging rights.

name: Oakland Chinatown
dealTitle: $29.50 for $59.00 - Oakland Chinatown Food & Culture Tour With Savor Oakland
dealinfo: Home to a variety of Asian immigrants, Oakland's Chinatown is bursting with fascinating tastes, sights and sounds from Vietnam, Cambodia, China and elsewhere. Explore them all on this three-hour walking tour, led by a friendly and knowledgeable Savor Oakland guide who'll help you break through cultural and language barriers for an authentic culinary adventure. Your visit to one of the city's oldest neighborhoods also offers a look at some of the area's historic landmarks and specialty stores, along with insider info on local customs and folklore.

name: The Flight Deck
dealTitle: COMP  for $8.00  - Improv Show for Children: Your Favorite Storybook Brought to Life
dealinfo: Bring your kids to an innovative kind of children's theater experience that brings their favorite bedtime story to life.  Once Upon Your Mind  is Oakland's premiere improvisation space for children and their families of the Bay Area. Every week at The Flight Deck, hear a new story that you and your kids get to choose from. Based on the actors' imaginations and your suggestions, they will re-write the story in a way that's never been told before. Things will get silly. Things will get creative, but most importantly, things will get interactive and fun. You may even be asked to volunteer during the show to play your favorite character. From pirates in space to a family on the farm, there's no telling where or what you can do at  Once Upon Your Mind. You get to explore and develop the kind of story you love to tell.

name: Spice Monkey
dealTitle: $5.00  for $10.00  - "Comedy Oakland" Stand-Up Showcase
dealinfo: One of the city's longest-running weekly shows,  Comedy Oakland  has been bringing you top headliners, local heroes and up-and-coming stars since way back in '09. Sit back and have a drink or a snack at the Spice Monkey, where you'll be entertained by faces you've seen on Comedy Central, HBO, BET, all the late-night talk shows, along with competition winners and stand-ups who've performed on "every habitable continent. "  Comedy Oakland  is produced by the world's only Indian-Jewish comedian, Samson Koletkar, aka Mahatma Moses, and is often hosted by  Date Talk  podcaster Ira Summer.

name: Gondola Servizio
dealTitle: $55 -- Private Gondola Ride for 2 w/Wine on Lake Merritt

name: Lake Chalet
dealTitle: $19.50 for $39.00 - "The Amazing Lake Merritt Scavenger Hunt": Fun For All Ages
dealinfo: Get outdoors and celebrate San Francisco's rich maritime history as you work with your teammates to solve puzzles and search for clues in a mad dash for the finish line. You'll visit a series of landmarks and complete a variety of fun challenges. Along the way, you'll have to snap pics of people or sights common to the area. A handy smartphone app will feed you challenges and clues, and it'll save your answers and photos in one place. It's a fun and active way to see the area around Lake Merritt!

name: alaMar

disclaimer: Valid during merchant's operating hours. Not valid during special events, such as Restaurant Week. Valid for two or more diners only. Dine-in only. Seasonal items subject to change. Not valid on products. Must be of legal age to consume alcohol. Cannot combine with other offers, including happy hour. Must use in one visit.
dealinfo: $30 for $60 worth of food and drinks for dinner $20 for $40 worth of food and drinks (alcoholic and/or non-alcoholic) for lunch Dish options include coconut shrimp lollipops, braised angus oxtail derived from Chef Nelson's mother's recipe and garnished oysters (ask for the Tabasco "caviar" from their secret menu) [**Click here**](http://www.alamaroakland.com/#!menus/c20aj)**** to see the menus Blackout dates: April 30 - May 1

name: Grace Temple Church
dealTitle: $7.50 for $15.00 - Potent Drama "Hurt Village" Observes Life in a Housing Project
dealinfo: A bold, gritty, heart-wrenching drama, Katori Hall's  Hurt Village  makes its Bay Area premiere at Oakland's Grace Temple Church. The story centers on a Memphis housing project after a government Hope Grant ignites the relocation of its residents. In the middle of it all is Cookie, a 13-year-old girl who aspires to be a professional rapper in the face of her seemingly insurmountable socio-economic situation. She lives in a community ravaged by drug addiction and violence and cheapened by empty government promises. Life is one unceasing existential crisis for this young black girl, as she and her family struggle to relocate and improve their way of life in a society where virtually no value is placed upon their lives.

name: Altarena Playhouse
dealTitle: COMP  for $26.00 - "Playing My Hand" Explores One Woman's Love Affair With Poker
dealinfo: "I'm a poker player. " Those are the words with which Rachel LePell introduces herself in  Playing My Hand. Rachel had a loving family, a beautiful home, a successful career . and a big secret. Traveling from the present into her past, this intimate and expansive play follows the ups and downs of the wild ride her penchant for poker has made of her life. At times humorous, at other times painful, this daring new show dives deep into a love affair with the thrill of winning. Catch this one-woman show, written and performed by Rachel LePell, at the Altarena Playhouse in Alameda.

name: Juhu Beach Club
dealTitle: $55.00 for $92.00 - "Temescal Tastes": A Culinary Walking Tour With Edible Excursions
dealinfo: Temescal is a cool hipster area of North Oakland, centered around Telegraph Avenue. One of the city's oldest neighborhoods, its commercial heart has emerged as a regional eating destination, home to innovative offerings in a culturally diverse community known for its artsy vibe. On this three-hour walking tour from Edible Excursions, find out where these food purveyors got their start -- whether at pop-up restaurants, fine-dining establishments, or farmers' market stands -- and learn about their edible businesses and commitment to providing fare with flair. Don't worry about getting hungry, as you'll have the opportunity to taste such goodies as handmade doughnuts, small-batch sorbet, grilled cheese, Baja-style fish tacos, Korean tofu stew and Indian street food.

name: Oakland Coliseum
dealTitle: $20.00  for $35.00  - NFL Preseason Football: Seattle Seahawks vs. Oakland Raiders
dealinfo: The Oakland Raiders take on their old nemeses from the AFC West -- and one of the best teams in football -- when the Seattle Seahawks come to the Oakland Coliseum. With head coack Jack Del Rio calling the shots, and a core of young talent centered around Derek Carr, Amari Cooper and Khalil Mack, the Raiders are poised to make a move this year, with playoff success a real possibility. The Seahawks, of course, are no strangers to post-season success, with four consecutive trips to the playoffs under their belts, including one Super Bowl win and one loss.

name: Niebyl-Proctor Library
dealTitle: $12.00 for $24.00 - Folk Singer Talia Cooper ("Anthem of the Pacifist Fascist") and Dessert Bar
dealinfo: Come for a night of decadent desserts and original, sassy and bold folk music presented by singer-songwriter-activist Talia Cooper at the Cozy Concert & Supper Club. With a voice comparable to Joni Mitchell, Cooper has been singing and writing songs since a young age. She frequently interweaves her original tunes with creative covers in humorous and sassy tones that address false cliches, love and her family traditions of activism. Folk comrades Maia "Papaya" Wiitala and Jeffrey Landau will also be joining Cooper at the Niebyl-Proctor Library in Oakland, and a three-item dessert bar is to follow. After listening, feast on sweet treats like pecan pie bars and dark chocolate fudge brownies. Live music has never sounded so delicious.

name: Aurora Theatre Company
dealTitle: $16.00  for $32.00  - Athol Fugard's Tony-Winning ""Master Harold" ... and the boys"
dealinfo: Aurora Theatre Company in Berkeley performs South African playwright Athol Fugard's critically-acclaimed drama  "Master Harold" . and the boys. An ordinary rainy afternoon in 1950s South Africa turns into a profound and life-changing experience for young, white Harold and the two black workers employed by his family. Alone and faced with the return of his alcoholic father, Harold must weigh his father's racist outlook against the respect he has for these men whom he considers his friends. Winner of the Tony Award for Best Play in 1982, and initially banned in South Africa,  "Master Harold" . and the boys  remains one of the most powerful coming-of-age plays ever written.

name: Peet's Theatre at Berkeley Rep
dealTitle: $50.00 for $60.00 - John Leguizamo's One-Man Show "Latin History For Morons"
dealinfo: Following the unabashed and uncensored tradition of his acclaimed solo shows  Ghetto Klown  and  Freak , Emmy and Obie Award winner John Leguizamo brings his latest personal venture  Latin History for Morons  to Peet's Theatre at Berkeley Rep, where he'll break down 3,000 years of cultural history into 90 minutes of irreverent comedy and outrageousness. Filled with Leguizamo's trademark humor, the piece follows the performer's attempt to educate his own son (as well as the audience) about the marginalization of Latinos throughout US history, while also emphasizing the significant roles they have played in the foundation of America. From a satirical rundown of the Aztec and Incan empires to vivid accounts of Latin patriots in the Revolutionary and Civil War, Leguizamo's cultural crash course is equal parts eye-opening and hysterical.

name: Social Hall SF
dealTitle: COMP  for $21.70  - Live Music at Social Hall SF
dealinfo: For the best live music entertainment, head to Goldenvoice's Social Hall SF in the Regency Ballroom building. Having recently undergone extensive renovation, the intimate space accommodates up to 600 and hosts electronic club nights, comedy events, rock concerts and more. Upgrades include a state-of-the-art sound system, a concert stage, and a 40-foot wooden bar where you can order a variety of specialty cocktails. From indie-rock to jazz, electronic to hip-hop, the venue's calendar is fast filling with great shows -- most of which are open to all ages. Score your tickets now to an upcoming show or three.

name: Woodminster Amphitheater
dealTitle: $20.00  for $30.00  - "Chicago": Tony-Winning Musical Under the Stars
dealinfo: Chicago  has everything that makes Broadway great: sizzling songs, seductive dance numbers and a show biz story that packs a powerful punch -- and seeing it outdoors at Oakland's Woodminster Amphitheater only amps up the show's famous red-hot razzle-dazzle. Set amidst the showy decadence of the 1920s,  Chicago  tells the tale of convicted murderers Roxie Hart and Velma Kelly, who'll stop at nothing to get the attention of the press and celebrity attorney Billy Flynn. Their malicious crimes turn them into media darlings, producing a barrage of sensational headlines, the likes of which could just as easily be ripped from today's tabloids. A smash on Broadway (winning six Tony Awards) and on the big screen (winning six Academy Awards), this biting satire features the unforgettable songs of Kander and Ebb, including "All That Jazz," "Cell Block Tango" and many more hits.
